<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="LinqReferencePro.Views.SettingsPage">
    <ContentPage.Content>
        <VerticalStackLayout>
            <Image Source="images/linq_logo2.png"/>

            
            <Label FontAttributes="Bold" FontSize="15" Padding="10">About</Label>
            <Label Padding="10" x:Name="labelAboutDesc" FontSize="12">
                I have experienced many languages, c, c++, java, python, swift, javascript..  but didn't see a languages that has a beautiful features like C#. Untill the .net version 2.0 C# was not so shiny and mature enough, however, after LINQ has been introduced in version 3.5 it dominates world of computer languages.  I always wanted to make an reference application to check whenever I want to. The LINQ PRO is to help and make you understand better to access LINQ technologies.  I tried to give more examples for better easier understanding. Hope you enjoy the app for your happier daily development works. This app will continuously updated with new articles.
            </Label>


            <Button
                x:Name="butResetFav"
                Text="Reset favorites"
                Padding="10"
                Margin="25"
                Clicked="OnClickReset"
            />

            <Label Padding="10" >
                Any questions or suggestion: linqpro@gmail.com
            </Label>
            
            <Label 
                Padding="10"
                VerticalOptions="Center" 
                HorizontalOptions="End" 
                FontSize="8">
                All rights reserved by Seho Park
            </Label>

            <Label FontAttributes="Bold" FontSize="15" Padding="10">Version History</Label>
            <Label Padding="10" FontSize="12" MaxLines="4">
                <Label.Text>
                    1.1 (5 Aug 23) Adding Previos/Next buttons. 
                    Sample code reorganized - SelectMany, Where, Take, TakeWhile, Skip, SkipWhile,Distinct, Join, 
                    GroupJoin, GroupBy, Except, Zip
                </Label.Text>
            </Label>
            <Label Padding="10" FontSize="12">
                1.0 - initial release
            </Label>

        </VerticalStackLayout>
        
    </ContentPage.Content>
</ContentPage>